king if the pipeline has actually changed since the last state snapshot at 17:06. The key change I'm seeing is that `cron:e7885813` ran for about a minute starting at 17:17 UTC and got aborted, but the consecutive errors counter was at 1 before that, so I need to verify whether this abortion represents a new error or just the normal cycle ending.\n\nLooking at the other sessions, `cron:ed2d0b5d` has finished its run and is marked as done, and the DTLX group is still running normally. Since there are no new failures beyond what was already tracked and the pipeline status remains healthy, this appears to be a stable state with no significant changes to report. 3 sessions (cron:6f3323ef ✅, cron:e7885813 ✅, telegram:group:-5163901258 ✅)\n- `cron:e7885813` had 1 error, but now it's reactivated and running (zombie cleared)\n\nThe only real change between the 17:06 and 17:20 snapshots is `cron:ed2d0b5d` finishing, which aligns with the 17:14 report mentioning it completed around 17:08. Since the last update already captured that completion, there's nothing new to report here—the pipeline's still healthy and stable. I'm tracing through the actual timestamps more carefully now. The heartbeat state file shows 17:06, but looking at the session data, the cron:e7885813 actually ended at 17:12:02 with an aborted error, not 17:16 as I thought. Let me verify the exact sequence of events across these sessions to get the timing right. I'm noticing that `cron:e7885813` shows as running in the heartbeat state from 17:06, but the session itself ended with an aborted error at 17:12 — this suggests the cron job re-triggered after that error and is currently running again, which matches what the 17:16 status report showed. Now I need to trace back what the heartbeat state looked like before 17:06 to understand the full sequence. Looking at the `cron:e7885813` session, it ended with an abort error after running for about 78 seconds, but the system still considers it \"running\" in the heartbeat state because the cron job itself is active and will likely retry. The recent 17:16 status report shows all three critical sessions running with the pipeline healthy, so there's no state change to report. I'm realizing the heartbeat state file I'm looking at is from an earlier check at 17:06, but the most recent status report was sent at 17:16 showing three active sessions with the pipeline healthy. Since my current check at 17:20 shows no changes from that baseline, there's nothing new to report."},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (17:20 UTC) against the heartbeat-state baseline (17:06 UTC) and the last 5p report (17:14 UTC):\n\n- `cron:6f3323ef` DTLX — still running ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` Agent Status — still running ✅ (aborted at 17:12, reactivated)\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — still active ✅\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` — completed (already noted at 17:14)\n- No new failures, no new blockers, no state transitions\n\n**No change from last stable state. Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":30623,"output":1231,"totalTokens":46229,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":431,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776187269852,"responseId":"062daa86e61456f3f2bde5f8f83ca71a","__openclaw":{"id":"694c6d9b","seq":5}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","label":"Cron: Agent Status to Lead","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776188085013,"sessionId":"e423b3ca-081c-4e83-a12e-dc2d2581ffe3","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":25646,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776187045063,"endedAt":1776188076580,"runtimeMs":157436,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/e4